Latin American Coffee Exports Gained 5.6% in June, Anacafe Says

-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-07-26T07:47:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/latin-american-coffee-exports-gained-5-6-in-june-anacafe-says.html
Coffee exports from  Colombia ,  Mexico 
and seven other Latin American countries climbed 5.6 percent
from a year earlier in June.  Total shipments rose to 2.46 million bags from 2.33 million
bags in June 2010, Guatemala’s National Coffee Association, or
 Anacafe , said in a report e-mailed yesterday. Deliveries gained
88 percent to 130,379 bags in  El Salvador  and increased 51
percent to 294,473 bags in Mexico.  Shipments from  Nicaragua  slid 47 percent to 115,119 bags.
Exports from Colombia, the world’s second-largest producer of
arabica beans, dropped 12 percent to 572,000 bags.  The following figures are from Anacafe, citing data from
the countries for production of mild washed arabica beans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
